fields.value: United States Congressional Roll Call Voting Records, 1789-1990:  Reformatted Data

dsDescriptionValue.value: Roll call voting records for the United States House of  Representatives and Senate through the 100th Congress are presented in  this data collection. Each data file in the collection contains  information for one chamber of a single Congress. The units of  analysis are the individual members of the House of Representatives  and Senate. Each record contains a member's voting action on every  roll call vote taken during that Congress, along with variables that  identify the member (e.g., name, party, state, and uniform ICPSR  member number). In addition, the codebook provides descriptive  information for each roll call, including the date of the vote,  outcome in terms of yeas and nays, name of initiator, the relevant bill or resolution number, and a synopsis of the issue.
